fields.title: Gitako
fields.description:
In the heart of rural Africa, farmers rise with the sun. They clear fields by hand, nurture the soil, and plant with hope—yet despite their efforts, many still face low yields, poor access to quality inputs, and limited markets for their produce. We believe it doesn’t have to be this way.

Gitako is our answer.

What is Gitako?

Gitako is an all-in-one AgricTech platform designed to empower smallholder farmers by giving them the tools to digitally manage their farms, access critical agricultural inputs, and sell directly to buyers—all from a single platform.

With Gitako, farmers can:

  • Track every activity from land clearing to harvesting

  • Get personalized recommendations for fertilizer, pesticides, and weed control based on their farm’s history or location

  • Access verified input suppliers to buy seeds, equipment, and fertilizers at fair prices

  • Sell their produce directly to off-takers and buyers through the Gitako marketplace

  • Monitor financial performance, track yields, and forecast production with ease

Why Gitako Matters

Africa is home to over 33 million smallholder farms, many of which operate without digital support. These farmers lose billions annually due to poor record keeping, lack of information, and middlemen who exploit them.

Gitako is more than a tool—it's a movement to digitally include every farmer, improve food security, and unlock the true potential of African agriculture.

We’re starting with pilot farms in Nigeria—and our early results are promising. One farm using Gitako increased yield tracking efficiency by over 60% and reduced input waste by 40%. Now, we want to bring Gitako to thousands more farmers.

Why We Need You

We’ve built the prototype. We’ve tested it. Now we need your support to:

  • Launch the Gitako mobile and web app across multiple regions

  • Onboard 1,000+ farmers in rural communities

  • Enhance the AI-based recommendation engine

  • Build a network of input suppliers and off-takers

Your backing will change lives—from the farmer planting cassava in Enugu to the woman leading her village’s first organized harvest group.

Join Us

We’re not just raising funds—we’re raising a movement. By supporting Gitako, you’re investing in a future where farmers are empowered, food systems are strengthened, and technology bridges the gap between potential and prosperity.

Together, let’s put power back in the hands of the people who feed us all.

Back Gitako. Grow the future.

fields.name: Michael Okafor
fields.content: "As an investor, I've found incredible opportunities on Ripple that I wouldn't have discovered elsewhere. The platform makes due diligence easy and transparent."

fields.name: Adeola Johnson
fields.content: Ripple helped me secure funding for my agritech startup when traditional investors wouldn't take a chance. Now we're expanding across three countries!

fields.name: Ruth Goodness
fields.content: As an investor, Ripple really aggregated the best crop of founders that could easily be managed and give great ROI.
